This paper is primarily focused on the safety analysis of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in domains such as autonomous driving and malware detection, which are related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper mentions the potential use of the proposed approach in guiding the training process of more robust neural networks, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
